WEBVTT

00:00:00.210 --> 00:00:02.820
[On-screen text] We believe technology can empower everyone to achieve more.

00:00:02.820 --> 00:00:06.920
[Audio description] A man uses a wheelchair equipped with a computer.
Narrator: We have so many pupils who are non-verbal but still have so much to say.

00:00:06.930 --> 00:00:10.020
Narrator: I want the exact same information that my hearing friends have.

00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:15.270
[Audio description] A young man signs his message.
Narrator: Barriers to communication are everywhere, but it's time to see them as opportunities.

00:00:15.270 --> 00:00:24.150
[Audio description] A woman with a headset and guide dog uses Soundscape technology to navigate.

00:00:24.150 --> 00:00:34.260
Narrator: Soundscape helps build a mental map of the environment through audio cues.

00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:39.720
[Audio description] A man uses eye control technology on a computer.
Narrator: With ALS, you can become locked in, but technology can give back communication.

00:00:39.720 --> 00:00:48.480
Narrator: Technology can restore independence where movement is limited.

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:54.300
[Audio description] A child uses symbols on a tablet.
Teacher: There is no better feeling than hearing a child say something they’ve always wanted to say.

00:00:54.300 --> 00:01:04.320
[Audio description] A student uses reading tools with adjusted spacing.
Student: Seeing space between words makes it easier to focus.

00:01:04.320 --> 00:01:12.480
Narrator: These tools can change lives and open new possibilities.

00:01:12.480 --> 00:01:20.610
[Audio description] A lecture hall using Microsoft Translator.
User: Now I can see exactly what was said. That’s been a huge help.

00:01:20.610 --> 00:01:30.840
Narrator: The system improves over time, helping students receive information in their preferred language.

00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:35.840
Narrator: Communication is essential for connection and belonging.

00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:48.240
[Audio description] An app converts speech into pictograms for a child with autism.
Parent: This helps build more spontaneous communication and relationships.

00:01:48.240 --> 00:02:00.090
[Audio description] A blind couple uses Seeing AI while raising their child.
Narrator: Seeing AI helps interpret the visual world, including their child’s school environment.

00:02:00.090 --> 00:02:10.230
Narrator: Artificial intelligence is already improving accessibility, but there is more to be done.

00:02:10.230 --> 00:02:20.370
Narrator: We're just getting started. Let’s see what you can do.

00:02:20.370 --> 00:02:24.871
[On-screen text] AI for Accessibility – Microsoft
